Salford Red Devils beat Wigan Warriors 24-18 in the Super League match . 
  Ben Jones-Bishop scored a spectacular solo try for the Red Devils . 
  Weller Hauraki and John Bateman were sent off for fighting in the second half . 
  Both sides ended the match with 12 men . 
  Salford ended a run of 17 defeats in a row against the Warriors . 
  Michael Dobson scored a try against his former club . 
 